        <h2>Help and Support</h2>
        <section>
            <h3>Getting Started</h3>
            <p>Welcome to the Budget Claims System. This guide will help you navigate through the system and make the most of its features.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Login:</strong> Use your credentials to log in to the system. If you don't have an account, contact your administrator.</li>
                <li><strong>Dashboard:</strong> After logging in, you will be redirected to your dashboard, where you can see an overview of your activities and tasks.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h3>Customer Functions</h3>
            <p>Customers can submit and view their claims through the customer portal.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Submit a Claim:</strong> Navigate to "Submit Claim" from the dashboard. Fill out the form with the required details including the MVA number and a description of the claim.</li>
                <li><strong>View Claims:</strong> To view submitted claims, go to "View Claims" from the dashboard. Here you can see the status and details of each claim.</li>
                <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Customers can update their account settings, change passwords, and manage 2FA from the "Settings" page.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h3>Employee Functions</h3>
            <p>Employees can manage claims and perform administrative tasks through the employee portal.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Manage Claims:</strong> Employees can view, edit, and update claims. Go to "Manage Claims" to access the list of all claims.</li>
                <li><strong>Search Claims:</strong> Use the "Search Claims" feature to filter and find specific claims based on various criteria such as MVA, customer name, status, and date range.</li>
                <li><strong>Reports:</strong> Generate reports from the "Reports" page. You can export data in CSV, Excel, and PDF formats.</li>
                <li><strong>User Management:</strong> Admins and managers can manage user accounts by navigating to "User Management." Here, you can create, delete, and update user roles and permissions.</li>
                <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Employees can update their account settings, change passwords, and manage 2FA from the "Settings" page.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h3>Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)</h3>
            <p>For added security, the Budget Claims System supports two-factor authentication.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Enable 2FA:</strong> Go to "Settings" and click "Enable 2FA." Follow the instructions to scan the QR code with your authenticator app and verify the token.</li>
                <li><strong>Disable 2FA:</strong> If you no longer want to use 2FA, go to "Settings" and click "Disable 2FA."</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h3>Notifications</h3>
            <p>The system provides notifications for various events.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Email Notifications:</strong> You will receive email notifications for important events such as new claims, status updates, and reminders for pending tasks.</li>
                <li><strong>In-App Notifications:</strong> Notifications will also be displayed within the system for real-time updates.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h3>Activity Logs</h3>
            <p>All user activities are logged for auditing purposes.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>View Logs:</strong> Admins can view activity logs to monitor user actions such as logins, claim submissions, edits, and deletions.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
